event-log-and-audit-trail.summary.md).\\\\n\\\\nVerification: `pytest backend/tests/test_event_log_service.py backend/tests/test_session_service.py` passed (`10 passed`), `pytest backend/tests` passed (`36 passed`), and `ruff check backend/app backend/tests` passed. No browser checks or screenshots were run because this prompt only changed backend/domain code. I made a checkpoint commit for the implementation as `9ca7cc4` (`feat(prompt-15): event log and audit trail`).\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"agent_message\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"item.completed\\\"}, \\\"task_display_context\\\": {\\\"event_number\\\": 195, \\\"prompt_index\\\": 16, \\\"prompt_name\\\": \\\"15 \\\\u2014 Event Log and Audit Trail\\\", \\\"prompt_total\\\": 100}, \\\"timestap\\\": \\\"2026-03-31T23:54:02-07:00\\\"}\\nprompts/15-event-log-and-audit-trail.yolopilot.jsonlines:196:{\\\"color\\\": \\\"bright_black\\\", \\\"emoji\\\": \\\"\\\\u2753\\\", \\\"event_type\\\": \\\"Unkown Event\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"{ \\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\": { \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"item_42\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"items\\\\\\\": [ { \\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\": false, \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Add event taxonomy models plus repository/service helpers for append-only session events and history reads\\\\\\\" }, { \\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\": false, \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Wire event logging into...\\\", \\\"raw_event\\\": {\\\"item\\\": {\\\"id\\\": \\\"item_42\\\", \\\"items\\\": [{\\\"completed\\\": false, \\\"text\\\": \\\"Add event taxonomy models plus repository/service helpers for append-only session events and history reads\\\"}, {\\\"completed\\\": false, \\\"text\\\": \\\"Wire event logging into current session mutations and expose backend session history loading\\\"}, {\\\"completed\\\": false, \\\"text\\\": \\\"Expand tests and docs for event taxonomy, replay assumptions, and helper usage\\\"}, {\\\"completed\\\": false, \\\"text\\\": \\\"Run targeted verification, commit checkpoints, and write the required task summary file\\\"}], \\\"type\\\": \\\"todo_list\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"item.completed\\\"}, \\\"task_display_context\\\": {\\\"event_number\\\": 196, \\\"prompt_index\\\": 16, \\\"prompt_name\\\": \\\"15 \\\\u2014 Event Log and Audit Trail\\\", \\\"prompt_total\\\": 100}, \\\"timestap\\\": \\\"2026-03-31T23:54:02-07:00\\\"}\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:13:  - Documented the fixed technical choices from the brief: React + Vite + TypeScript, Python + FastAPI, PostgreSQL, a file-backed GCS emulator, Docker Compose, backend-owned Gemini access, and `secrets.yaml` excluded from git.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:18:  - Captured the bedtime-story positioning, the sessions-first UX requirement, the staged workflow, the two-pane workspace, and the chat/UI bridge rules.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:22:  - Explained why Gemini calls must stay on the backend.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:38:  - The frontend must never hold provider secrets or call Gemini directly.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:39:  - Gemini usage should be isolated behind backend adapters for planning, long-form generation, and narration.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:43:  - PostgreSQL-backed job records, segment records, and event logs are part of the intended design.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:48:  - `docs/` now holds product and architecture intent.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:59:  - Example: if you are building pitch generation or beat-sheet editing, the product brief defines the required stage order and the expectation that chat and UI actions mirror each other.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:63:  - Example: if you later add Gemini integration, this doc already sets the boundary that secrets stay in `secrets.yaml` and model access stays behind backend services.\\nprompts/00-project-charter.summary.md:118:- The only Gemini-related changes were architectural documentation notes.\\nprompts/11-postgres-schema-and-m