 )\\\\n32 | | from app.models import WorkflowStage, WorkflowStageState\\\\n   | |________________________________________________________^\\\\n   |\\\\nhelp: Organize imports\\\\n\\\\nE501 Line too long (102 > 100)\\\\n   --> tests/test_db_models.py:131:101\\\\n    |\\\\n129 |             revision_number=1,\\\\n130 |             raw_brief=\\\\\\\"A sleepy fox rows across a moonlit lake.\\\\\\\",\\\\n131 |             normalized_summary=\\\\\\\"A bedtime-safe quest about crossing the lake to find a glowing reed.\\\\\\\",\\\\n    |                                                                                                     ^^\\\\n132 |             is_active=True,\\\\n133 |             accepted_at=now,\\\\n    |\\\\n\\\\nFound 3 errors.\\\\n[*] 2 fixable with the `--fix` option.\\\\n\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"/bin/zsh -lc 'cd backend && .venv/bin/python -m ruff check app tests'\\\", \\\"exit_code\\\": 1, \\\"id\\\": \\\"item_48\\\", \\\"status\\\": \\\"failed\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"command_execution\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"item.completed\\\"}, \\\"task_display_context\\\": {\\\"event_number\\\": 94, \\\"prompt_index\\\": 12, \\\"prompt_name\\\": \\\"11 \\\\u2014 PostgreSQL Schema and Database Migrations\\\", \\\"prompt_total\\\": 100}, \\\"timestap\\\": \\\"2026-03-31T22:50:25-07:00\\\"}\\nprompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.yolopilot.jsonlines:128:{\\\"color\\\": \\\"green\\\", \\\"emoji\\\": \\\"\\\\ud83d\\\\udcac\\\", \\\"event_type\\\": \\\"Agent Message\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"The live Postgres pass found a real bug in the Alembic environment: it still fell back to full app settings even when `STORYTELLER_DATABASE_URL` was set. I\\\\u2019m fixing that lookup path now so migrations can run without unrelated Gemini/GCS...\\\", \\\"raw_event\\\": {\\\"item\\\": {\\\"id\\\": \\\"item_67\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"The live Postgres pass found a real bug in the Alembic environment: it still fell back to full app settings even when `STORYTELLER_DATABASE_URL` was set. I\\\\u2019m fixing that lookup path now so migrations can run without unrelated Gemini/GCS settings.\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"agent_message\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"item.completed\\\"}, \\\"task_display_context\\\": {\\\"event_number\\\": 128, \\\"prompt_index\\\": 12, \\\"prompt_name\\\": \\\"11 \\\\u2014 PostgreSQL Schema and Database Migrations\\\", \\\"prompt_total\\\": 100}, \\\"timestap\\\": \\\"2026-03-31T22:52:13-07:00\\\"}\\nprompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.yolopilot.jsonlines:175:{\\\"color\\\": \\\"green\\\", \\\"emoji\\\": \\\"\\\\ud83d\\\\udcac\\\", \\\"event_type\\\": \\\"Agent Message\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"Implemented the first real SQLAlchemy/Alembic persistence layer for the backend: explicit ORM models for sessions, workflow stage state, briefs, pitches, character sheets, beat sheets, story setup, composition/audio jobs, composition seg...\\\", \\\"raw_event\\\": {\\\"item\\\": {\\\"id\\\": \\\"item_92\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Implemented the first real SQLAlchemy/Alembic persistence layer for the backend: explicit ORM models for sessions, workflow stage state, briefs, pitches, character sheets, beat sheets, story setup, composition/audio jobs, composition segments, export assets, and the event log, plus the initial migration at [20260331_01_initial_storyteller_schema.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/migrations/versions/20260331_01_initial_storyteller_schema.py). I also added shared DB base/session helpers, migration docs in [backend/README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md) and [backend/migrations/README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/migrations/README.md), and updated the architecture/domain docs to reflect the first-schema tradeoff of tracking accepted child rows on the child tables to avoid circular foreign keys.\\\\n\\\\nVerification passed end to end: `make check`, focused backend tests, SQLite Alembic cycle tests, and a live PostgreSQL `alembic upgrade head -> downgrade base -> upgrade head` run against the compose `postgres` service. No browser checks were needed because this prompt only changed backend persistence. The required reviewer summary is written at [11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md). Checkpoint commits: `16b904e` and `89ad342`.\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"agent_message\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"item.completed\\\"}, \\\"task_display_context\\\": {\\\"event_number\\\": 175, \\\"prompt_index\\\": 12, \\\"prompt_name\\\": \\\"11 \\\\u2014 PostgreSQL Schema and Database Migrations\\\", \\\"prompt_total\\\": 100}, \\\"timestap\\\": \\\"2026-03-31T22:55:18-07:00\\\"}\\nprompts/09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.summary.md:21:- Gemini calls stay backend-owned\\nprompts/09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.summary.md:44:- the browser must never call Gemini directly\\nprompts/09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.summary.md:61:- Gemini adapters\\nprompts/09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.summary.md:104:- append durable events that the API can expose to chat and UI\\nprompts/09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.summary.md:122:### Example 4: A future prompt that intentionally changes direction\\nbackend/tests/test_session_service.py:16:    EventLogEntry,\\nbackend/tests/test_session_service.py:75:        db_session.query(EventLogEntry)\\nbackend/tests/test_session_service.py:76:        .filter(EventLogEntry.session_id == snapshot.id)\\nbackend/tests/test_session_service.py:77:        .order_by(EventLogEntry.sequence_number.asc())\\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.ts:13:} from './chat/sessionChat.ts'\\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.ts:25:  origin: 'chat' | 'ui'\\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.ts:58:  chat: {\\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.ts:444:    chat: {\\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.ts:496:        chat: {\\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.ts:504:       